Sentencas: La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85, as a representative material belonging to La2BaIn2O7-based family, is a novel and promising electrolyte material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Defect chemistry and transportation within La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 mixed ionic-electronic conducting membrane: Towards the application of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, due to the co-existence of various mobile charged defects including oxygen vacancy, proton, and electron-hole, the conduction properties and behaviors of La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 are complex and not fully understood.
Titulo: Defect chemistry and transportation within La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 mixed ionic-electronic conducting membrane: Towards the application of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, we systematically explore La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 with a focus on defect chemistry and transportation.
Titulo: Defect chemistry and transportation within La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 mixed ionic-electronic conducting membrane: Towards the application of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A theoretical model is built to analyze the experimentally measured conductivities of La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 at varying temperatures and oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: Defect chemistry and transportation within La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 mixed ionic-electronic conducting membrane: Towards the application of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Subsequently, the conduction properties and behaviors of La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 membrane at open circuit conditions and operation conditions are investigated thoroughly for the first time.
Titulo: Defect chemistry and transportation within La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 mixed ionic-electronic conducting membrane: Towards the application of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our findings reveal that in reducing and humidified atmospheres, La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 behaves as a dual-ion conducting oxide, with oxygen-ionic transport numbers exceeding 0.7.
Titulo: Defect chemistry and transportation within La1.7Ba1.3In2O6.85 mixed ionic-electronic conducting membrane: Towards the application of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our work can provide a new and overall understanding of the La2BaIn2O7-based material for SOFCs' application.(c) 2023
